        "text": "Mmh, this looked simple in my head before you asked... :thinking_face: I think if there are plans for next version to be a patch version then yes, the r-release will pick that, but if next version is a minor upgrade it will remain as is (which I think is the intention of the R core). Maybe this section helps, specially the last paragraph: <https:\/\/contributor.r-project.org\/rdevguide\/chapters\/getting_started.html#the-r-source-code>\nAs uses go, I usually use the latest released R version, but that depends if your project\/work is tied to an R version or not.",
